$ .git/index

The `.git/index` file contains a list of all the files being tracked.

New files are added with `git add`, existing files removed with `git rm`. The content of the index is shown with `git ls-files`.

The current index file for the development/version-control-systems/git/repository[repository].

Usually not found in → development/version-control-systems/git/repository#bare.

sa:
  `→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/add`,
  `→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/apply`,
  `→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/checkout-index`
